<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ901224-0075</DOCNO><DOCID>901224-0075.</DOCID><HL>   Technology:   Texas Instruments, Samsung</HL><DATE>12/24/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE 12</SO><CO>   C.SEL TXN</CO><IN>SEMICONDUCTORS, INTEGRATED CHIPS (SEM)</IN><LP>   DALLAS -- Texas Instruments Inc. said it reached afive-year licensing agreement with Samsung Electronics Co. ofSouth Korea, settling one of several patent issues withforeign chip makers.   The company didn't disclose the amount of royalties itexpects to receive from Samsung but said the total will&quot;greatly exceed&quot; royalties under the chip makers' previousagreement, which expires at year end. The new agreement issubject to approval by the South Korean government.</LP><TEXT>   Several other licensing agreements between TexasInstruments and foreign chip makers expire at the end of thisyear, and the company said negotiations for new agreementswere continuing.</TEXT></DOC>